                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/7011.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-04-04T13:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 4, 1913—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>159. Intention to execute General Angeles being insistently reported. I
                    remonstrated yesterday at the Foreign Office against any such action, as I am
                    sure the General is not guilty of any crime. Mr. de la Barra said he would ask
                    the Government for guaranties of his life.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
